25|$|On August 2, 2007, McKinney {{participated in}} a press conference in New Orleans to launch an International Tribunal on Hurricanes <b>Katrina</b> <b>and</b> <b>Rita,</b> which she {{described}} as an effort to seek justice for the victims of those hurricanes and their aftermath.|$|E
25|$|Habitat {{has been}} criticized for its slow and inefficient {{rebuilding}} efforts along the Gulf Coast after Hurricanes <b>Katrina</b> <b>and</b> <b>Rita.</b> After 18months, Habitat had completed under 500homes. A major factor was Habitat's reliance on working through local affiliates, who are not equipped to undertake large-scale rebuilding efforts.|$|E
